      },
      "message": "Thank you for breaking that down,  I appreciate it.  Just to be clear, when you say the quote is solid with no surprises,  does that mean it's a binding quote?  And how long is this price valid for?  Also, are there any circumstances where the final bill could end up being higher than two thousand one hundred pounds,  for example if the move takes longer than expected or if there are any additional access issues on the day?\n \nI also have a quote from another firm for one thousand five hundred fifty pounds,  itemised and valid this week.  Would you be able to match or beat that price?",
